gurmukhi: ਛਬਿ ਕੈ ਅਨੇਕ ਛਬ ਸੋਭਾ ਕੈ ਅਨੇਕ ਸੋਭਾ ਜੋਤਿ ਕੈ ਅਨੇਕ ਜੋਤਿ ਨਮੋ ਨਮੋ ਨਮ ਹੈ
transliteration: Chhabi Kai Anayk Chhab Sobhaa Kai Anayk Sobhaa , Joti Kai Anayk Joti Namo Namo Nam Hai ?
translation: Myriad beauties and many praises salute the beauty and praise of divine effulgence of the True Guru.

gurmukhi: ੳੁਸਤੁਤਿ ੳੁਪਮਾ ਮਹਾਤਮ ਮਹਿਮਾ ਅਨੇਕ ੲੇਕ ਤਿਲ ਕਥਾ ਅਤਿ ਅਗਮ ਅਗਮ ਹੈ
transliteration: Ousatouti Oupamaa Mahaatam Mahimaa Anayka , Ayk Til Kadaa Ati Agam Agam Hai ?
translation: Praise of the True Guru equal to a sesame seed is beyond many praises, comparisons, and glories described.

gurmukhi: ਬੁਧਿ ਬਲ ਬਚਨ ਬਿਬੇਕ ਜੳੁ ਅਨੇਕ ਮਿਲੇ ੲੇਕ ਤਿਲ ਅਾਦਿ ਬਿਸਮਾਦਿ ਕੈ ਬਿਸਮ ਹੈ
transliteration: Budhi Bal Bachan Bibayk Jau Anayk Milay , Ayk Til Aadi Bisamaadi Kai Bisam Hai ?
translation: If all the wisdom, strength, powers of speech, and worldly knowledge combine, these would be astonished by a momentary initial glimpse of the True Guru.

gurmukhi: ੲੇਕ ਤਿਲ ਕੈ ਅਨੇਕ ਭਾਂਤਿ ਨਿਹਕਾਂਤਿ ਭੲੀ ਅਬਿਗਤਿ ਗਤਿ ਗੁਰ ਪੂਰਨ ਬ੍ਹਮ ਹੈ ||੧੪੧||
transliteration: Ayk Til Kai Anayk Bhaanti Nihakaanti Bhaee , Abigati Gati Gur Pooran Braham Hai ?141?
translation: All the beauties become insipid and fade away before a momentary glimpse of the divine light of the True Guru. Therefore grandeur of complete God like True Guru is beyond apprehension. (141)
